HEADWORD: Reigle
<hw>Rei"gle</hw> <pr>(r?"g'l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>r⟦egrave⟧gle</ets> a rule, fr. L. <ets>regula</ets>. See
<er>Rule</er>.]</ety> <def>A hollow cut or channel for quiding anything;
<as>as, the <ex>reigle</ex> of a side post for a flood gate</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Carew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

